.TH "sfwbar-wifi" "1" "" ""
.SH Name
sfwbar-wifi \- Sfwbar Wifi interface
.sp
Filename: wifi\-iwd.so
Filename: wifi\-nm.so
.sp
Requires: none
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sp
Wifi module interface provides means to query and control the wifi network
connections.  There are currently two modules providing this interface:
wifi\-iwd provides support for IWD daemon and wifi\-nm provides support for
NetworkManager.
.sp
\fB* In order to use wifi\-iwd module, the user must have permission to control
iwd daemon. Usually permissions are granted by adding the user to \(ganetdev\(ga or
\(gawheel\(ga user group *\fP
.SH Triggers
.sp
The module defines the following triggers:
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B wifi\-level
This signal is emitted when signal strength for the current connection
changes.
.TP
.B wifi\-conf
this trigger is emitted when a new wireless network is discovered or
properties of a network have changed. Once the trigger is emitted.
Functions handling this trigger can access variable \fIid\fP containing the id
of the network.
.TP
.B wifi\-conf\-removed
this trigger is emitted when a network is no longer available and should be
removed from the layout.  Functions handling this trigger can access variable
\fIid\fP containing the id of the network.
.TP
.B \(dqwifi\-scan\(dq
this trigger is emitted when scan for networks has been initiated.
.TP
.B \(dqwifi\-scan\-complete\(dq
this trigger is emitted when scan for networks is complete.
.UNINDENT
.SH Functions
.SS WifiGet(ID, Property)
.sp
Function WifiGet queries a property of a network specified by parameter \fIID\fP
The supported properties are:
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \(dqSSID\(dq
an SSID of the network. Returns <string>
.TP
.B \(dqType\(dq
a Type of the network. Returns <string> (\(aqopen\(aq, \(aqwep\(aq, \(aqpsk\(aq or \(aq8021x\(aq)
.TP
.B \(dqKnown\(dq
an indcator of whether this is a known network. Returns <boolean>.
.TP
.B \(dqStrength\(dq
signal strength of the network. Returns <numeric> (0..100)
.TP
.B \(dqConnected\(dq
an indicator of whether the daemon is connected to the network.
Returns <boolean>
.UNINDENT
.SS WifiScan([<Duration>])
.sp
Initiate scan for wireless networks. An optional <numeric> parameter specifies
duration of a scan in seconds.
.SS WifiConnect(<ID>)
.sp
Attempt to connect to a network specified by the \fIID\fP\&.
.SS WifiDisconnect(<ID>)
.sp
Disconnect from a network specified by the \fIID\fP\&.
.SS WifiForget(<ID>)
.sp
Forget a known network specified by the \fIID\fP\&.
